---
import MCPHeader from '../../components/MCPHeader.astro';
import "../../styles/global.css";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en" class="dark">
    <head>
        <meta charset="UTF-8" />
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
        <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
        <title>About - MCP Center</title>
        <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
        <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
        <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
    </head>
    <body class="min-h-screen bg-slate-900 text-white transition-colors duration-300 m-0 w-full h-full font-sans">
        <MCPHeader />
        
        <main class="container mx-auto py-8 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-5xl">
            <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
                <div class="bg-slate-800/70 backdrop-blur-sm border border-cyan-500/50 shadow-lg shadow-cyan-500/30 rounded-xl p-8 transition-colors duration-300">
                    <h2 class="text-lime-300 text-4xl mb-8 pb-3 border-b border-fuchsia-500/50 font-bold drop-shadow-[0_0_8px_rgba(190,242,100,0.5)]">About MCP Center</h2>
                    
                    <div class="space-y-6">
                        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-cyan-300">
                            MCP Center is your enterprise gateway to the Model Context Protocol (MCP) ecosystem. Built on Azure API Center, 
                            we provide a scalable, secure, and reliable platform for discovering, managing, and deploying MCP servers across 
                            your organization.
                        </p>

                        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-cyan-300">
                            The Model Context Protocol enables seamless integration between AI applications and various data sources, tools, 
                            and services. Whether you need to connect to GitHub repositories, databases, file systems, or custom enterprise 
                            APIs, MCP Center provides a unified registry to discover and manage these connections.
                        </p>

                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-pink-300 mt-8 mb-4">Key Features</h3>
                        
                        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-yellow-300">
                            <li>Centralized registry for all your MCP servers</li>
                            <li>Enterprise-grade security and compliance</li>
                            <li>Support for both local and remote MCP servers</li>
                            <li>Integration with Azure services and Microsoft ecosystem</li>
                            <li>Partner ecosystem for extended capabilities</li>
                            <li>Easy discovery and deployment</li>
                        </ul>

                        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-cyan-300 mt-6">
                            Built on Azure API Center's robust infrastructure, MCP Center ensures your AI applications have reliable, 
                            secure, and scalable access to the resources they need to deliver intelligent experiences to your users.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="mt-12 flex justify-center gap-4">
                        <a href="/mcp" class="px-6 py-3 bg-gradient-to-r from-cyan-500 to-blue-500 hover:from-cyan-400 hover:to-blue-400 text-white rounded-lg transition-all duration-300 shadow-lg shadow-cyan-500/50 hover:shadow-cyan-500/70 flex items-center">
                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 mr-2" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
                                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M9.707 14.707a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414l4-4a1 1 0 011.414 1.414L7.414 9H15a1 1 0 110 2H7.414l2.293 2.293a1 1 0 010 1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                            </svg>
                            Back to MCP Center
                        </a>
                        <a href="/mcp/onboard" class="px-6 py-3 bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-500 to-fuchsia-500 hover:from-pink-400 hover:to-fuchsia-400 text-white rounded-lg transition-all duration-300 shadow-lg shadow-fuchsia-500/50 hover:shadow-fuchsia-500/70 flex items-center">
                            Get Started
                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 ml-2" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
                                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M12.293 5.293a1 1 0 011.414 0l4 4a1 1 0 010 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414-1.414L14.586 11H3a1 1 0 110-2h11.586l-2.293-2.293a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                            </svg>
                        </a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
        </main>
    </body>
</html>
